TITLE: Creating Products with Predefined UUID
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a product with a predefined UUID and associated category in Shopware 6.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/guides/plugins/plugins/framework/data-handling/writing-data.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function writeData(): void
{
    $context = Context::createDefaultContext();

    $productId = Uuid::randomHex();

    $this->productRepository->create([
        [
            'id' => $productId,
            'name' => 'Example product',
            'productNumber' => 'SW127',
            'stock' => 10,
            'tax' => $this->getTaxId($context),
            'price' => [['currencyId' => Defaults::CURRENCY, 'gross' => 50, 'net' => 25, 'linked' => false]],
            'categories' => [
                [
                    'id' => Uuid::randomHex(),
                    'name' => 'Example category'
                ]
            ]
        ]
    ], $context);
}
```

