TITLE: Validating POST Requests in PHP for Shopware App System
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code snippet shows how to manually verify the signature of POST requests from Shopware. It calculates the signature using the request body and app secret, then compares it with the signature provided in the request header.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/guides/plugins/apps/app-signature-verification.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Psr\Http\Message\RequestInterface;

/** @var RequestInterface $request */
$queryString = $request->getUri()->getQuery();
$signature = hash_hmac(
    'sha256',
    $request->getBody()->getContents(),
    $appSecret
);

// reset the stream pointer, so the body can be read again
$request->getBody()->rewind();
$compare = $request->getHeader('shopware-shop-signature')[0];

// validate with compare signature from Shopware
$valid = hash_equals($signature, $compare);
```

