TITLE: Extending Media File Extension Whitelist in Shopware PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a subscriber class that adds a custom file extension to Shopware's media file extension whitelist. It subscribes to the MediaFileExtensionWhitelistEvent and adds the 'img' extension to the allowed list.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/guides/plugins/plugins/content/media/add-custom-file-extension.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Swag\BasicExample\Service;

use Shopware\Core\Content\Media\Event\MediaFileExtensionWhitelistEvent;
use Symfony\Component\EventDispatcher\EventSubscriberInterface;

class Subscriber implements EventSubscriberInterface
{
    public static function getSubscribedEvents(): array
    {
        return [
            MediaFileExtensionWhitelistEvent::class => 'addEntryToFileExtensionWhitelist'
        ];
    }

    public function addEntryToFileExtensionWhitelist(MediaFileExtensionWhitelistEvent $event): void
    {
        $whiteList = $event->getWhitelist();
        $whiteList[] = 'img';

        $event->setWhitelist($whiteList);
    }
}
```

