TITLE: Step 3: Deprecating Constants and String Parameters
DESCRIPTION: Adding deprecation notices to constants and method parameters to signal the future removal of string-based API in the next major version.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/resources/references/adr/2023-05-16-php-enums.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Indexer
{
    // @deprecated tag:v6.6.0 - Constant will be removed, use enum IndexMethod::PARTIAL
    public const PARTIAL = 'partial';
    // @deprecated tag:v6.6.0 - Constant will be removed, use enum IndexMethod::FULL
    public const FULL = 'full';

    /**
     * @deprecated tag:v6.6.0 - Parameter $method will not accept a primitive in v6.6.0
     */
    public function product(int $id, IndexMethod|string $method): void
    {
        if (is_string($method)) {
            $method = match ($method) {
                'partial' => IndexMethod::PARTIAL,  
                'full' => IndexMethod::FULL,
                default => throw new \InvalidArgumentException()
            };
        }

        match ($method) {
            IndexMethod::PARTIAL => $this->partial($id),
            IndexMethod::FULL => $this->full($id)
        };
    }
}
```

