TITLE: Implementing the extractId Method for a Custom Context Resolver in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet demonstrates a sample implementation of the `extractId` method in a custom `AclContextResolver`. It checks the type of the `$context` object (e.g., `ContactIdentity`, `OwnershipContext`, `ContactEntity`) and extracts the relevant ID. If the context object type is not supported, it throws an `AclUnsupportedContextException`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/products/extensions/b2b-suite/guides/core/entity-acl.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function extractId($context): int
{
    if ($context instanceof ContactIdentity) {
        return $context->getId();
    }

    if ($context instanceof OwnershipContext && is_a($context->identityClassName, ContactIdentity::class, true)) {
        return $context->identityId;
    }

    if ($context instanceof ContactEntity && $context->id) {
        return $context->id;
    }

    throw new AclUnsupportedContextException();
}
```

