TITLE: Step 2: Converting String Parameters to Enum Instances
DESCRIPTION: Implementation that handles string values by converting them to enum instances, allowing both API styles to work simultaneously.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/resources/references/adr/2023-05-16-php-enums.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Indexer
{
    public const PARTIAL = 'partial';
    public const FULL = 'full';

    public function product(int $id, IndexMethod|string $method): void
    {
        if (is_string($method)) {
            $method = match ($method) {
                'partial' => IndexMethod::PARTIAL,  
                'full' => IndexMethod::FULL,
                default => throw new \InvalidArgumentException()
            };
        }

        match ($method) {
            IndexMethod::PARTIAL => $this->partial($id),
            IndexMethod::FULL => $this->full($id)
        };
    }
}
```

