TITLE: Fine-tuning Cache Invalidation in Shopware PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code snippet shows how to selectively remove specific event listeners from the CacheInvalidationSubscriber in Shopware. It uses the RemoveEventListener class to target and remove particular event-method pairs, allowing for more granular control over cache invalidation behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/guides/hosting/performance/custom-cache-invalidation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace MyProject;

use Shopware\Core\Content\Product\Events\ProductIndexerEvent;
use Shopware\Core\Content\Product\Events\ProductNoLongerAvailableEvent;
use Shopware\Core\Framework\DependencyInjection\CompilerPass\RemoveEventListener;
use Shopware\Core\Framework\Adapter\Cache\CacheInvalidationSubscriber;

class TweakCacheInvalidation implements CompilerPassInterface
{
    public function process(ContainerBuilder $container): void
    {
        RemoveEventListener::remove(
            $container,
            CacheInvalidationSubscriber::class,
            [
                [ProductIndexerEvent::class, 'invalidateListings'],
                [ProductNoLongerAvailableEvent::class, 'invalidateListings'],
            ]
        );
    }
}
```

