TITLE: Adding a Deprecated Public Function in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a new public method to an abstract class that will become abstract in a future version, using proper deprecation annotations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/resources/guidelines/code/backward-compatibility.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
/** Before */
abstract class AbstractProductRoute
{
    abstract public function getDecorated(): AbstractProductRoute;

    abstract public function load();
}


/** After */
abstract class AbstractProductRoute
{
    abstract public function getDecorated(): AbstractProductRoute;

    abstract public function load();

    /**
     * @deprecated tag:v6.5.0 - Will be abstract 
     */
    public function loadV2()
    {
        return $this->getDecorated()->loadV2();
    }
}
```

