TITLE: Defining and Using Native Enums for Methods - PHP (PHP 8.1+)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates PHP 8.1's native enum feature by modeling method options as strict enum cases and typehints, ensuring type safety and exhaustive handling. No manual validation or in_array checks are needed. Integrates cleanly with match expressions and allows for extensibility, serialization, and additional methods. Requires PHP 8.1 or higher.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/resources/guidelines/code/core/6.5-new-php-language-features.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
enum IndexMethod
{
    case PARTIAL;
    case FULL;
}

class Indexer
{
    public function product(int $id, IndexMethod $method): void
    {
        match ($method) {
            IndexMethod::PARTIAL => $this->partial($id),
            IndexMethod::FULL => $this->full($id)
        };
    }
}
```

