TITLE: ACL Query Filter Implementation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of ACL filtering for database queries using the QueryBuilder with support for ownership context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/products/extensions/b2b-suite/guides/core/entity-acl.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace My\Namespace;

use Doctrine\DBAL\Query\QueryBuilder;
use Shopware\B2B\Acl\Framework\AclUnsupportedContextException;
use Shopware\B2B\StoreFrontAuthentication\Framework\OwnershipContext;

protected function applyAcl(OwnershipContext $context, QueryBuilder $query): void
{
    try {
        $aclQuery = $this->aclRepository->getUnionizedSqlQuery($context);

        $query->innerJoin(
            self::TABLE_ALIAS,
            '(' . $aclQuery->sql . ')',
            'acl_query',
            self::TABLE_ALIAS . '.id = acl_query.referenced_entity_id'
        );

        foreach ($aclQuery->params as $name => $value) {
            $query->setParameter($name, $value);
        }
    } catch (AclUnsupportedContextException $e) {
        // nth
    }
}
```

