TITLE: Subscriber Implementation for All Config Fields as SCSS Variables
DESCRIPTION: Extends the ThemeVariableSubscriber to automatically convert all plugin configuration fields to SCSS variables. Uses a name converter to transform camelCase names to kebab-case for proper SCSS naming conventions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/guides/plugins/plugins/storefront/add-scss-variables-via-subscriber.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Swag\BasicExample\Subscriber;

// ...
use Symfony\Component\Serializer\NameConverter\CamelCaseToSnakeCaseNameConverter;

class ThemeVariableSubscriber implements EventSubscriberInterface
{
    // ...

    public function onAddVariables(ThemeCompilerEnrichScssVariablesEvent $event): void
    {
        $configFields = $this->systemConfig->get('SwagBasicExample.config', $event->getSalesChannelId());

        foreach($configFields as $key => $value) {
            // convert `customVariableName` to `custom-variable-name`
            $kebabCased = str_replace('_', '-', (new CamelCaseToSnakeCaseNameConverter())->normalize($key));

            $event->addVariable($kebabCased, $value);
        }
    }
}
```

