TITLE: Initial Implementation Using Constants
DESCRIPTION: Example of a class using string constants to define valid indexing methods with validation logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/resources/references/adr/2023-05-16-php-enums.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Indexer
{
    public const PARTIAL = 'partial';
    public const FULL = 'full';

    public function product(int $id, string $method): void
    {
        if (!in_array($method, [self::PARTIAL, self::FULL], true)) {
            throw new \InvalidArgumentException();
        }

        match ($method) {
            self::PARTIAL => $this->partial($id),
            self::FULL => $this->full($id)
        };
    }
}
```

