TITLE: Defining Custom Approval Rule Condition in manifest.xml for Shopware App
DESCRIPTION: This XML snippet defines a custom approval rule condition in the manifest.xml file of a Shopware app. It specifies the condition's identifier, name, group, script file, and constraints for the UI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopware/docs/blob/main/products/extensions/b2b-components/order-approval/guides/04-add-new-approval-condition.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<rule-condition>
    <identifier>cart_amount_rule_script</identifier>
    <name>Total cart amount</name>
    <group>cart</group>
    <script>/approval-rule-conditions/custom-condition.twig</script>
    <constraints>
        <single-select name="operator">
            <options>
                <option value="<">
                    <name>Is less than</name>
                </option>
                <option value="<=">
                    <name>Is less than or equal to</name>
                </option>
                <option value="=">
                    <name>Is equal to</name>
                </option>
                <option value=">=">
                    <name>Is greater than or equal to</name>
                </option>
                <option value=">">
                    <name>Is greater than</name>
                </option>
            </options>
        </single-select>
        <float name="amount">
            <placeholder>Enter amount</placeholder>
        </float>
    </constraints>
</rule-condition>
```

